snippet.textDisplay: Alright, people saying that YouTube Kids exist, here is the problem. There is a big gap between YT Kids and YT. YT Kids displays content for kids below school age. (Below 7-9 years). The type of content there consists of nursery rhymes and toy reviews. This means that kids around 9-12 years of age are trapped between this gap in content. As YT has a wider range of content that appeals to older kids (mainly gaming), older kids will naturally move to YT instead, as content in YT Kids don’t interest them. Thus, YT Kids won’t solve the problem.
